text:
if you've ever felt sad
if you've ever felt alone
like a fuckin alien because some idiot, decided to touch you like an object, talk to you like an object, you are not alone.

i am young, i am young and dumb like everyone else. people may think us small, insignificant, silly- but we are fucking brilliant. i'm sick of being quiet, i'm sick of suffering in silence, so i'd like to present a project that's sprung to mind, i've been wanting to do something to raise awareness and support of those who've been assaulted.. but i never know how or where to start.  if you reference, my previous post about assault-the positivity and support it gained was unimaginable.

i have never felt so strong, so powerful, so.. human, happily human- sense my assault which was three plus years ago.

so i want you, to share your stories. you don't have to go in detail, hell, just say "i'm ____ and i've been assaulted/harrassed." i want to make a movement. to spread awareness. to post that yes, it happens- but no.. no we are not quiet. we are not good little victims we are not dead we are not broken we are just struggling.

but we come out stronger than anyone can imagine.

and maybe you find me 'extra' maybe you find me an 'attention whore' milking assault for attention. but i call this rebellion, i call this decency, i call this a cry of love and hope into a bareen wasteland of.. of silence. of people who are so painfully polarized 
give this project a name, give it a home comment, message me, tag me in posts, tag yungblud, tag you're friends, tag ian, i want to see you're polygraph eyes! i want to see your scars! i want you to understand that those scars are battle wounds not detrimental markers of him or her. 
if anyone is interested in helping out with this project, message me as well. i'm going to post more details on this soon, loves ğŸ–¤

i love you.
we love you.
this is what the black hearts club looks like.
this is what the mother fuckin' youth looks like.
âœŠğŸ–¤

text:
i was standing 
before 
you,
wearing my skin only
and you touched my nudity, 
as you left some burns.
my body is a temple, 
it is transcendent, 
but it shrunk under your gaze,
so brutally tender
and i got lost in the maze of its chambers.

out of my dignity,
you were stripping me slowly,
out of my dignity and out of my mind
so if you spit in a temple, 
will it seize to be holly?
will it seize to be a shelter 
for something sacred,
for something i used to call â€œsoulâ€? at home i washed my skin 
and i hung it to dry,
then my angels laid down
to console my demons, 
to say we are as clean as 
before 
you. (17.07.17) #poetry #metoo #canva

#whyididntreport 
because i was 8 years old and i was scared and ashamed of what was being done to me. the people that sexually abused me as a child were my family members. it was my grandmother and my biological father. i was 14 years old when i reported to the police that my father had sexually abused me for 5 years. my family immediately disowned me. they didnâ€™t believe me and they protected my father. i was unwanted and abandoned by everyone. the police believed me because there was sufficient physical evidence of the abuse. but i never mentioned my grandmotherâ€™s sexual abuse because i didnâ€™t think that her sexual assault counted as sexual abuse. there was no real penetration just oral copulation and touching by my grandmother.  however, the judicial system always looks for â€œevidenceâ€ and there was no evidence to prove what my grandmother had done to me when i was 8 years old. there are many reasons that survivors donâ€™t tell anyone about the sexual abuse or the rape inflicted upon them. itâ€™s been many years after the sexual abuse and i recently had a flashback of my father sexually abusing me when i was three years old. i will never be able to tell you when the sexual abuse begun as a child. i canâ€™t tell you the time, what he/she was wearing during each assault on me. i canâ€™t give you a chronological timeline of the events. does this make me a liar? no. i was too busy dissociating and surviving this horrific assault to my dignity, mind, body and soul.

#thereasonwhyididntreport
